summary: This is an email chain regarding scheduling and transcript ordering for a Final Pretrial Conference (FPTC) in the case U.S. v. Ghislaine Maxwell. The correspondence is between court personnel and the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS).

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: The subject of the criminal case referenced in the email chain (U.S. v. Ghislaine Maxwell).

events.title: Final Pretrial Conference for U.S. v. Ghislaine Maxwell
events.description: A Final Pretrial Conference (FPTC) scheduled to take place for 4 hours beginning at 9:30 AM.

keyFacts: The document is an email chain about logistical arrangements for a Final Pretrial Conference in the Ghislaine Maxwell criminal case.
The FPTC was scheduled for November 23, 2021, the day after the email was sent.
The U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS) was involved in ordering the transcript for same-day delivery.
The case is identified as 20CR330, U.S. v. Ghislaine Maxwell.
